run host name against all servers


ansible multi -a “hostname”
ansible multi -a “hostname” -f 1 (run without any more forrks					
ansible multi -a "df -h” (disk space available)
ansible multi -a “date” (check date is in sync)
ansible multi -a “free -m” (check free memory)					
ansible multi -s -m yum -a "name=ntp state=present” (installation) 
ansible multi -s -m service -a "name=ntpd state=started enabled=yes” (starting a service)